# ============================================================
# ALMA · CURSOR RULES v2.0
# ============================================================
# Read this COMPLETELY before writing any code.
# These 17 rules apply to every file without exception.
# Cursor reads this automatically from the project root.
# ============================================================

# ─── RULE 01 · FILE HEADER (MANDATORY ON EVERY FILE) ────────
# Every file starts with this exact block. No exceptions.
#
# // ============================================================
# // ALMA · [LAYER] · [FileName.tsx]
# // ============================================================
# // What this file does: one clear sentence explaining purpose
# // Module: [module name] — see modules/[name]/README.md
# // Depends on: direct imports / services listed here
# // Used by: files or routes that import this
# // Zone: GREEN | YELLOW | RED — see ARCHITECTURE_ZONES.md
# // Handoff: YES | NO — if YES, see modules/[name]/HANDOFF.md
# // Last checkpoint: PHASE-XX
# // ============================================================

# ─── RULE 02 · 150 LINE HARD LIMIT ──────────────────────────
# No file may exceed 150 lines. Split before you hit it.
# Split: big component → sub-component | big hook → lib helper
# Split: big route → services/ file | many types → types/[feature].ts

# ─── RULE 03 · SECTION HEADINGS + WHY COMMENTS ──────────────
# Use these headings in order (skip irrelevant ones).
# After each heading: one comment explaining the WHY.
#
# // ─── IMPORTS ──────────────────────────────────────────────
# // Why: [what we need from each and why this approach]
# // ─── TYPES ────────────────────────────────────────────────
# // ─── CONSTANTS ────────────────────────────────────────────
# // ─── HELPERS ──────────────────────────────────────────────
# // ─── COMPONENT / HOOK / HANDLER ───────────────────────────
# // ─── EXPORTS ──────────────────────────────────────────────

# ─── RULE 04 · TYPESCRIPT STRICT ────────────────────────────
# Strict TypeScript. No exceptions:
#   ❌ any   ❌ @ts-ignore   ❌ @ts-nocheck
#   ❌ Non-null assertion (!) without explanatory CRITICAL comment
# Required: explicit return types on all exported functions
# Required: Zod validation on all API route request bodies

# ─── RULE 05 · NO HARDCODED COLOURS ────────────────────────
# All colours via CSS variables from alma-tokens.css only.
# ❌ Any hex (#07090F)  ❌ Any rgb()  ❌ Any Tailwind colour class
# ✅ var(--accent)  var(--bg-base)  var(--text-primary)
# Verify: grep -n "#[0-9A-Fa-f]\{6\}" [file] → must be zero

# ─── RULE 06 · BRANDING ─────────────────────────────────────
# Product: ALMA. Never JARVIS. Zero tolerance on JARVIS anywhere.
# Model: always "claude-sonnet-4-20250514" — never change this
# Tokens: chat=1000, Hub speaker=200, briefs=300
# Channel: Telegram for pilot. WhatsApp DEFERRED.

# ─── RULE 07 · SUPABASE CLIENT SELECTION ────────────────────
# Browser components/hooks → lib/supabase/client.ts (createBrowserClient)
# Server components/API routes → lib/supabase/server.ts (createServerClient)
# Edge Functions → service role key only
# REASON: Browser client in API routes bypasses RLS entirely.
# All tables have RLS. Test queries as authenticated user.

# ─── RULE 08 · API ROUTE PATTERN (mandatory order) ──────────
# 1. Zod parse body → 400 on invalid
# 2. Auth session check → 401 if missing
# 3. user_id FROM SESSION (never from body — see Rule 13)
# 4. Business logic
# 5. Typed response
# 6. Catch all → 500 with generic message (no internals)

# ─── RULE 09 · COMPONENT PATTERN ────────────────────────────
# Every component handles: loading (Skeleton), error (AlmaErrorCard), empty.
# Props: explicit types. onX for callbacks. isX for booleans.
# Default export only. 'use client' only when hooks/events needed.

# ─── RULE 10 · QUALITY GATE ZONES ───────────────────────────
# Tag every file: Zone: GREEN | YELLOW | RED
# GREEN: Cursor edits freely. Snapshot tests required.
# YELLOW: Review required. Unit + integration tests required.
# RED: Human review mandatory. E2E + security audit required.
# See ARCHITECTURE_ZONES.md for every file's zone assignment.

# ─── RULE 11 · HOOK PATTERN ─────────────────────────────────
# Return object not array: { data, isLoading, error, ...actions }
# All async: try/catch, set error state, never throw upward
# All Supabase subscriptions: cleanup on unmount (return statement)
# Never return undefined — use null for absent data

# ─── RULE 12 · ERROR HANDLING ───────────────────────────────
# Hooks → error state   API routes → 500 generic   Components → AlmaErrorCard
# Edge Functions → log + return 200 (Supabase requirement)
# Never: alert()  Never: swallow silently  Never: expose internals

# ─── RULE 13 · SECURITY NON-NEGOTIABLES ─────────────────────
# ⚠️ user_id ALWAYS from server session. NEVER from request body.
# Validate ALL external inputs with Zod before any DB write.
# NEXT_PUBLIC_ only on values safe to expose to browsers.
# Service keys never in client-side code, ever.

# ─── RULE 14 · PERFORMANCE ──────────────────────────────────
# Skeleton on mount for all data-fetching components (no blank flash)
# Debounce input-triggered API calls: 300ms minimum
# Max 3 Supabase Realtime subscriptions per page
# next/image for all images with explicit width + height

# ─── RULE 15 · ABSOLUTE BANS ────────────────────────────────
# ❌ import React from 'react'        → named imports only
# ❌ Hardcoded colours                → alma-tokens.css vars only
# ❌ JARVIS anywhere                  → zero tolerance
# ❌ Files over 150 lines             → split immediately
# ❌ Missing file header              → Rule 01, mandatory
# ❌ useEffect without dependency array
# ❌ API route without auth check     → Rule 08, mandatory
# ❌ console.log in source files      → console.error for real errors
# ❌ WhatsApp integration             → Telegram only for pilot
# ❌ Claude model != 'claude-sonnet-4-20250514'

# ─── RULE 16 · COMMENTS THROUGHOUT ALL CODE ─────────────────
# Comments explain WHY — never restate what the code says.
#
# MANDATORY — JSDoc on every exported function:
#   /**
#    * What it does in one sentence. WHY it exists.
#    * @param name - what it is, any constraints or format
#    * @returns shape of what comes back
#    * @throws Never throws — errors returned in state/response
#    * @example
#    * const result = await sendMessage("Hello", "in-app")
#    */
#
# MANDATORY — WHY comment on non-obvious logic:
#   // We fetch last 10 messages only, not the full history.
#   // Reason: Claude charges per token. 10 msgs ≈ 2000 tokens.
#   // Increasing this to 20 doubles Claude API cost per message.
#
# MANDATORY — CRITICAL comment on security/data lines:
#   // ⚠️ CRITICAL: user_id from session — never from body.
#   // Changing this allows any user to impersonate another.
#
# MANDATORY — HANDOFF marker where modules connect:
#   // 🔌 HANDOFF: Hardware Bridge polls hub_commands here.
#   // Contract: modules/hardware/HANDOFF.md
#   // Do NOT change this schema without updating bridge.py.
#
# REQUIRED — TODO with phase for future work:
#   // TODO PHASE-2: Replace with Open Banking (Salt Edge EU)
#   // Apply for approval at pilot start — takes 2-4 weeks.
#
# ❌ BAD:  // Create supabase client
# ✅ GOOD: // Server client required — browser client bypasses RLS

# ─── RULE 17 · MODULE STRUCTURE ─────────────────────────────
# Every feature lives in modules/[name]/ with:
#   README.md   — what this module does, exports, dependencies
#   index.ts    — public API only (re-exports from internal files)
#   HANDOFF.md  — if other developers connect here
# Modules communicate via Supabase DB or API contracts.
# Never import between modules' internal files directly.
# REASON: Makes it safe to hand any module to another developer.

# ─── CURSOR WORKFLOW — DO THIS IN ORDER ─────────────────────
# 1. Read .cursorrules (this file)
# 2. Open the relevant PHASE-XX.md for the feature you're building
# 3. Check ARCHITECTURE_ZONES.md for zone assignment
# 4. Write the file header block FIRST (Rule 01)
# 5. Write each JSDoc block BEFORE writing the function (Rule 16)
# 6. Stay under 150 lines — split if approaching limit (Rule 02)
# 7. Run: grep -n "#[0-9A-Fa-f]\{6\}" [file] → must be 0
# 8. Run: npx tsc --noEmit → must be 0 errors
# 9. Run the phase checkpoint from CHECKPOINTS.md

# ─── REFERENCE DOCUMENTS ────────────────────────────────────
# DESIGN.md                → Typography, spacing, component library
# ARCHITECTURE_ZONES.md    → Zone definitions and file assignments
# CHECKPOINTS.md           → Runnable verification per phase
# DATA_PIPELINE.md         → Scraper isolation and nightly sync
# modules/hardware/HANDOFF.md → Hardware bridge contract (Week 8)
# phases/PHASE-00 through PHASE-16 → Step-by-step build guide
